title: For Sale/Trade:  Savage Model 10 BA Stealth
postcontent: Savage Model 10 BA Stealth in 6.5 Creedmoor. Incredibly accurate rifle with only 40 rounds through it. I started the Savage recommended barrel break in, but didn't see any reason to continue the full break in procedure. The pictured target is a 1 inch square shot from a bench with bipod and rear hand bag only. No lead sled. This was at 100 yards with a full value wind sustained at 30 mph, with gusts to 40. Thing is, the wind blew the right side of the target off the staples, so with each gust the wind would double the target over onto itself, so each shot had to be timed. Great practice but this gun is even more precise in calm conditions. I'm hesitant to trade, but I don't have any place to stretch this rifle out as it deserves. Looking to trade the gun itself, or can trade with any combination of/or all of the additions.
